# Steps to Dockerize Spring boot application. 

1. Create a Dockerfile in your project. ( Please take a reference of file added in this folder )
2. Downlaod and Install Docker Desktop apllication in local.
3. Sign In with your credential.
4. Open command prompt and navigate to project location or In IDE, Right click the application and click to open in terminal. 
5. Type the following commands in terminal 
  5.1 - mvn clean package  Note: once successfully build. 
  5.2 - docker build --tag=[application name]:latest .
  5.3 - docker run -p8080:8080 [application name]:latest 

Your application will start running in provided endpoint. In this case, It will run in http://localhost:8080/
